BEVO Digital Art: Asset-Backed NFT Protocol
Project Overview: Strategic Tokenization of Physical Fine Art
Architect: Bevon Reyaz Babwah

Status: Launched (2021) | Peak Valuation: ~$2M (combined ecosystem)

üöÄ Executive Summary for Recruiters
BEVO Digital Art was a pioneering 2021 project on the Binance Smart Chain (BSC) designed to solve the "speculative value" problem of NFTs. Unlike standard digital-only collections, BEVO architected a protocol where digital tokens were legally and physically bound to tangible art assets (paintings, sculptures, etc.).


This project demonstrates a candidate who can:


Design High-Stakes Systems: Architected a 7-year liquidity lock to secure asset value under volatile market conditions.



Lead Multi-Disciplinary Projects: Managed a team of 6 core developers while overseeing GTM strategy across global regions.



Bridge Reality & Web3: Created the "BEVO Verification and Minting Standard v1.0" to bring legacy art houses into the digital economy.


üõ†Ô∏è Technical & Product Innovation
1. The Minting & Verification Standard v1.0
Bevon designed a tiered system for asset tokenization that mirrors complex data-handling protocols:


Level 1 (Digital-Only): Frictionless minting for photographs and videos using ERC-721/1155 standards.


Level 2 (Traditional Art): A proprietary process where an NFT represents exclusive ownership of a physical piece. The token is "bound" to the physical asset, ensuring no split-ownership conflicts.



Asset Vaulting: To support this, the project roadmap included the establishment of physical "Art Houses" in New York, London, and Paris for high-security storage.


2. Economic Engineering (Tokenomics)
The project utilized a low-friction 8% transaction fee model optimized for capital preservation:


2% Deflationary Burn: Permanent supply reduction to drive scarcity.



2% Reflections: Automated static rewards distributed to all token holders.


4% Growth Fund: Explicitly allocated for artist onboarding, dAPP development, and the "Save the Arts" scholarship.



üìä Business & GTM Strategy

Scale: Successfully led presale campaigns and social media onboarding for artists from diverse global cultures.


Strategic Partnerships: Identified and approached top-tier exchanges like BitMart and WhiteBit for liquidity expansion.


Compliance & Trust: Implemented a rigorous vetting procedure (ID verification, ownership certification, and copyright audit) to prevent fraud in high-value asset trading.

üí° Why This Matters for Tech Leadership
This whitepaper serves as "Proof of Work" that Bevon can:

Translate Complexity: Convert the abstract concept of blockchain into a tangible business model (Art Tokenization).


Navigate Ambiguity: Establish trust in a nascent market through transparent fund allocation and third-party contract audits.



Think Long-Term: While most 2021 projects were "short-term plays," Bevon architected a 7-year roadmap for global expansion into markets like Cairo, Egypt.
